The paper deals with graph theory and specifically focuses on the independence number, matching size, and critical difference of graphs. These topics are commonly studied in computer science subfields such as discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and combinatorial optimization (cs.CO). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
